&quot;Overall, the game mode is popular and the queue is healthy (meaning enough players are participating that the wait for a game isn&rsquo;t long), so we don&rsquo;t want to do too much that might have the risk of making ARAM less popular.
That said, we don&rsquo;t think the way champion assignment is working out has aged well. We aren&rsquo;t fans of the ARAM accounts that some players make in order to have a more limited champion pool, since that kind of defeats the purpose. So we do discuss whether we should have the pool apply not just to owned and free champions, but to all champions (or maybe even a large subset of all champions that we cycle through over time).&quot;

In base a queste dichiarazioni di Ghostcrawler, secondo voi questi cambiamenti verranno (spero) effettuati in un futuro prossimo o lontano? E secondo voi quanto potrebbero essere positivi per quella modalit&agrave;?
